Carnival & Lent. Bottom Left: on the back of one of the men throwing dice - a mirror. What does this mean? Look up:
G. [Gustav] F. Hartlaub, Zauber des Spiegels. [Geschichte und Bedeutung des Spiegels in der Kunst], München [R. Piper] 1951;
H. [Heinrich] Schwarz, 'The Mirror in Art', in: Art Quarterly 1952, N° 15, p. 97;

Idem, 'The Mirror of the Artist and the Mirror of the Devout' in: [Paul A. Underwood (ed.)], Studies of the History of Art dedicated to W.E. Suida [on his eightieth birthday ], [London: Phaidon], 1959, p. 90; Suzanne Sulzberger, Considérations sur le chef-d'œuvre de Quentin Metsys: Le prêteur et sa femme, Musées R. des Beaux-Arts de Belgique-Bulletin, XIV, 1965, pp. 27-34, especially pp. 31 ff.
